The USD50m HDD disposal deal that didn’t work out is good for the company. The management suddenly woke up and realised that the HDD business generated S$45m in the last 18 months and still have run way to generate more cash for the next few years as its main customer Seagate’s business has improved due to more orders for enterprise HDD which has better margin. The Shenzhen building is worth S$45m to 50m while its book value is only S$18m. This is 6 cents a share gain if disposed.
Seagate business slow down in 2nd half.  So probably be cautious abit.
